The k-th type of omics data are denoted as Xij(k) (the row index represents the i-th molecular feature and the column index represent the j-th sample), while Θ(k) denotes the size-matched parameter matrix of X(k). The probabilistic model specifies the probability density (mass) function of the observations given the parameters for each data type as below:
