For integrative analysis, there are two or more observed data matrixes X(k) (k = 1, 2, …, K). Thus the overall parameter matrix Θ stacks all the parameter matrices (Θ(k)) used for each observed data matrix. The overall likelihood function is the sum of the likelihood functions of different data types:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
